      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/57/1208",
      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ يُصَلِّي بِقَوْمٍ رَكْعَتَيْنِ ثُمَّ أَخْبَرَهُمْ أَنَّهُ لَيْسَ عَلَى وُضُوءٍ قَالَ «يُتِمُّ اَلْقَوْمُ صَلاَتَهُمْ فَإِنَّهُ لَيْسَ عَلَى اَلْإِمَامِ ضَمَانٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1208 - Jamil ibn Darraj narrated from Zurarah, from one of the Imams (as) who said:\n\"I asked him about a man who leads a congregation for two rak'ahs and then informs them that he was not in a state of wudu' (ritual purity).\nImam (as) said: 'The congregation should complete their prayer because the Imam bears no responsibility (for their prayers).'\"."
        ]
      }
    },
